-Let's go.

260
00:25:29.994 --> 00:25:30.718
(GROWLS)

261
00:25:30.853 --> 00:25:32.387
Excuse you. sir.

262
00:25:35.665 --> 00:25:37.963
I'm synthetic.
I was built and deployed

263
00:25:38.098 --> 00:25:40.736
by the Weyland-Yutani
Corporation for research.

264
00:25:40.872 --> 00:25:43.304
Because their humans wouldn't
last a day on this planet.

265
00:25:43.440 --> 00:25:44.334
(CHUCKLES)
We found that--

266
00:25:44.470 --> 00:25:46.006
(THUDS)

267
00:25:46.142 --> 00:25:47.501
(SIGHS)

268
00:25:49.277 --> 00:25:51.145
(GRUNTS)

269
00:25:51.280 --> 00:25:53.208
Look... (SIGHS)

270
00:25:53.344 --> 00:25:56.317
Many Yautja have come
for the great Kalisk.

271
00:25:56.453 --> 00:25:58.888
and none have survived it...

272
00:25:59.024 --> 00:26:00.250
or Genna.

273
00:26:01.058 --> 00:26:02.318
(SIGHS)

274
00:26:03.459 --> 00:26:05.321
I've seen the Kalisk.

275
00:26:05.998 --> 00:26:07.488
I survived it.

276
00:26:08.898 --> 00:26:11.366
Here's my proposal:
You take me along with you.

277
00:26:11.501 --> 00:26:14.104
and I'll guide you to its den.

278
00:26:14.239 --> 00:26:16.435
Once there. I get my legs.

279
00:26:16.570 --> 00:26:18.373
you get your trophy.

280
00:26:18.508 --> 00:26:21.403
and everyone's a winner. Deal?

281
00:26:27.418 --> 00:26:31.248
Oh. yeah. I've seen the Kalisk.

282
00:26:34.157 --> 00:26:35.417
(SCOFFS)

283
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:37.926
(DEVICE BEEPS. WHIRS)

284
00:26:38.062 --> 00:26:41.599
(SIGHS)

285
00:26:43.233 --> 00:26:44.525
Okay. Hmm.

286
00:26:45.832 --> 00:26:47.962
-(GROWLS)
-(THIA SIGHS)

287
00:26:48.098 --> 00:26:49.563
Good luck with your journey.

288
00:26:51.070 --> 00:26:54.876
I'm just gonna...
go on my journey.

289
00:26:57.208 --> 00:26:58.979
I'm sure
you'll figure something out.

290
00:27:06.058 --> 00:27:08.582
Hey. (PANTING)

291
00:27:10.059 --> 00:27:12.894
I've already shown you
that I can be useful to you.

292
00:27:19.030 --> 00:27:23.002
Yes. Yes. exactly. like a tool.

293
00:27:23.138 --> 00:27:25.503
The only way to survive Genna
is to work with it.

294
00:27:25.638 --> 00:27:27.309
and I know how.

295
00:27:27.444 --> 00:27:30.604
And with the right tool...

296
00:27:32.208 --> 00:27:33.750
...you could get the Kalisk.

297
00:27:34.748 --> 00:27:35.950
You could be the first.

298
00:27:41.624 --> 00:27:43.859
You may call me Thi-- Whoa!

299
00:27:45.259 --> 00:27:48.930
You seem smaller than the other
Yautja. How old are you?

300
00:27:50.566 --> 00:27:51.996
And what does the chewing?

301
00:27:52.132 --> 00:27:54.463
Your outside fangs
or your inside teeth?

302
00:27:56.298 --> 00:27:58.632
Oh. What should I call you?

303
00:28:02.445 --> 00:28:03.813
-(GRUNTS)
-(YELPS)

304
00:28:04.776 --> 00:28:06.850
Whoa! (LAUGHS)

305
00:28:06.985 --> 00:28:09.718
I've never been thrown before.
What a... (DISTORTS) ...thrill!

306
00:28:09.854 --> 00:28:12.151
How fast were you going
when your ship crashed?

307
00:28:12.287 --> 00:28:15.459
Faster than sub-light speed?
We haven't cracked that yet.

308
00:28:15.594 --> 00:28:17.656
Also. that plasma sword
is interesting.

309
00:28:17.791 --> 00:28:19.294
Is it unique to your clan?

310
00:28:19.430 --> 00:28:21.698
And what may I call you?

311
00:28:21.867 --> 00:28:24.460
-I call these<i> imbre anguis.</i>
-(PROJECTILES HISSING)

312
00:28:34.212 --> 00:28:36.412
(PANTING)

313
00:28:36.547 --> 00:28:37.880
THIA: They just want a snack.

314
00:28:42.352 --> 00:28:45.415
(SQUEAKING)

315
00:28:45.551 --> 00:28:48.420
You catch more flies with honey
than you do with vinegar.

316
00:28:48.556 --> 00:28:50.222
(BUZZING)

317
00:28:52.359 --> 00:28:56.163
Predatory organisms are
my specific area of expertise.

318
00:28:56.298 --> 00:28:59.430
I've studied Yautja extensively.
It's an impressive culture.

319
00:28:59.566 --> 00:29:01.099
(SIGHS)

320
00:29:01.235 --> 00:29:03.196
Here. ask me anything.
I bet I have the answer.

321
00:29:03.331 --> 00:29:04.603
-(EXHALES)
-Oh! (THUDS)

322
00:29:04.739 --> 00:29:06.009
(ANIMALS CALL DISTANTLY)

323
00:29:06.145 --> 00:29:07.610
Very funny.

324
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:09.175
And you still haven't
told me your name.

325
00:29:35.273 --> 00:29:37.373
Okay. sure.

326
00:29:38.109 --> 00:29:42.069
(SIGHS) Well. let's back up
and start at the beginning.

327
00:29:42.538 --> 00:29:45.607
Genna was formed
64 billion cycles ago.

328
00:29:45.742 --> 00:29:48.414
when a dying red dwarf star
in a neighboring system...

329
00:29:48.550 --> 00:29:50.612
(BEEPING)

330
00:29:55.755 --> 00:29:57.927
(WHIRRING)

331
00:29:59.628 --> 00:30:01.264
(CLICKING. WHIRRING)

332
00:30:01.399 --> 00:30:03.429
It's so beautiful.

333
00:30:04.132 --> 00:30:06.601
After all the time
I've been stuck here.

334
00:30:06.736 --> 00:30:08.564
I never get tired of the view.

335
00:30:12.539 --> 00:30:16.007
Well. we arrived on Genna two
years ago. and we built a base.

336
00:30:16.142 --> 00:30:18.512
Then. I was in
the vulture's nest

337
00:30:18.648 --> 00:30:20.582
for the most exciting

338
00:30:20.717 --> 00:30:23.617
13 days. seven hours. 43 minutes

339
00:30:23.753 --> 00:30:25.583
and two seconds of my life.

340
00:30:25.719 --> 00:30:27.283
(EXHALES)

341
00:30:27.418 --> 00:30:29.123
But I always knew
someone would come.

342
00:30:30.386 --> 00:30:32.522
I was just wrong about who.

343
00:30:39.303 --> 00:30:40.497
Tessa.

344
00:30:42.137 --> 00:30:45.540
Our crew is made up
entirely of synths.

345
00:30:45.676 --> 00:30:47.506
But Tessa and I are special.

346
00:30:48.275 --> 00:30:50.507
We have a higher sensitivity
than the others.

347
00:30:56.614 --> 00:30:58.818
Sensitivity is what allows us
to understand

348
00:30:58.953 --> 00:31:00.550
the creatures on this planet.

349
00:31:04.421 --> 00:31:06.457
We were created
to work in tandem.

350
00:31:07.460 --> 00:31:11.461
Me. cooped up in the lab.
Tessa out in the field.

351
00:31:11.597 --> 00:31:14.733
Until the wonderful day
Tessa let me come with her.

352
00:31:14.869 --> 00:31:16.907
We were exploring Genna.

353
00:31:18.643 --> 00:31:21.538
And then the Kalisk attacked us.

354
00:31:22.679 --> 00:31:26.015
Separated me... and us.

355
00:31:29.017 --> 00:31:31.818
The last sound
I remember hearing

356
00:31:31.953 --> 00:31:35.156
was Tessa calling out my name.

357
00:31:35.987 --> 00:31:37.554
Reaching for me.

358
00:31:39.562 --> 00:31:41.063
Then the Kalisk.

359
00:31:42.567 --> 00:31:43.934
I didn't know what to do.

360
00:31:45.469 --> 00:31:48.862
(DEK SNORING)

361
00:31:55.407 --> 00:31:57.871
But I refuse
to believe she's dead.

362
00:32:00.517 --> 00:32:05.417
(BEEPING)

363
00:32:10.693 --> 00:32:15.362
(HYDRAULICS HISSING)

364
00:32:15.498 --> 00:32:16.131
(THUDS)

365
00:32:17.534 --> 00:32:19.596
(WHIRRING)

366
00:32:24.105 --> 00:32:25.701
-(CLICKS)
-(ELECTRONIC WARBLE)

367
00:32:33.882 --> 00:32:35.614
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

368
00:32:35.750 --> 00:32:36.551
(GUNFIRE)

369
00:32:36.686 --> 00:32:38.956
Thia. Thia. Thia...

370
00:32:39.921 --> 00:32:42.257
THIA:<i> Tessa!</i> (YELLING)

371
00:32:42.393 --> 00:32:43.257
(ROARS)

372
00:32:43.859 --> 00:32:46.053
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

373
00:32:46.189 --> 00:32:47.428
Thia. Thia.

374
00:32:47.564 --> 00:32:50.594
(WHIRRING)

375
00:32:56.804 --> 00:32:58.734
(WHIRRING)

376
00:33:06.814 --> 00:33:08.909
(BUZZING)

377
00:33:18.597 --> 00:33:20.427
(ELECTRONIC CHIRPING)

378
00:33:20.563 --> 00:33:22.626
(GASPS)

379
00:33:24.667 --> 00:33:26.931
(WHIRRING)

380
00:33:27.133 --> 00:33:29.033
MUTHUR:<i> Hello. Tessa.</i>

381
00:33:29.235 --> 00:33:31.800
<i>The Company is not pleased.</i>

382
00:33:33.806 --> 00:33:36.970
<i>Continued failure will result</i>
<i>in your decommission.</i>

383
00:33:40.749 --> 00:33:42.283
Where's Thia?

384
00:33:45.922 --> 00:33:47.618
MUTHUR:<i> The Yautja has Thia.</i>

385
00:33:51.157 --> 00:33:54.361
(CREATURES CHITTERING)

386
00:33:56.599 --> 00:33:58.631
(CAWING)

387
00:33:58.767 --> 00:34:01.333
(IN YAUTJA)

388
00:34:01.469 --> 00:34:03.997
THIA: Two warriors.
Dek and Thia. on the hunt.

389
00:34:04.771 --> 00:34:06.343
Oh.

390
00:34:06.478 --> 00:34:08.038
Quick question.

391
00:34:08.174 --> 00:34:09.311
What should I be doing?

392
00:34:09.447 --> 00:34:11.172
(CHUFFS)

393
00:34:11.307 --> 00:34:12.874
(ANIMAL GROWLS)

394
00:34:17.351 --> 00:34:19.553
THIA: Bone bison.
They're Kalisk food.

395
00:34:19.689 --> 00:34:21.389
(GROWLING)

396
00:34:21.524 --> 00:34:25.190
DEK:

397
00:34:25.326 --> 00:34:28.524
So exciting.
Hunting with a Yautja.

398
00:34:28.659 --> 00:34:29.696
-(GROWLS)
-Tessa wouldn't believe it.

399
00:34:29.831 --> 00:34:31.024
(CHUFFS. CLICKS)

400
00:34:32.167 --> 00:34:33.235
-Just a warning...
-(GROWLS)

401
00:34:36.508 --> 00:34:37.668
(YELPS. GROWLS)

402
00:34:38.710 --> 00:34:39.440
(QUIETLY) Razor grass.

403
00:34:39.576 --> 00:34:41.001
(CLINKS)

404
00:34:43.511 --> 00:34:46.039
It'll cut you to ribbons.
We'll just go around.

405
00:34:52.988 --> 00:34:54.921
(CREATURE CHITTERING)

406
00:34:55.257 --> 00:34:57.391
We might not be alone
in this hunt.

407
00:34:58.563 --> 00:35:01.023
(BEEPING)

408
00:35:01.159 --> 00:35:02.231
(WHIRRING)

409
00:35:04.098 --> 00:35:06.367
-(HISSES)
-(SHOUTS)

410
00:35:08.002 --> 00:35:09.232
What an odd critter.

411
00:35:09.368 --> 00:35:11.141
I've never seen you before.

412
00:35:11.608 --> 00:35:12.802
(HISSES)

413
00:35:14.006 --> 00:35:15.805
(ROARS)

414
00:35:17.045 --> 00:35:18.742
Thia. Nice to meet you.

415
00:35:19.412 --> 00:35:20.910
-(SCOFFS)
-(SPRINGING CLICK)

416
00:35:21.046 --> 00:35:22.317
(GRUNTS)

417
00:35:23.412 --> 00:35:25.782
(GROWLS. ROARS)

418
00:35:32.597 --> 00:35:34.295
(CLICKING)

419
00:35:34.430 --> 00:35:35.596
Looks like your competition
is better-- (GASPS)

420
00:35:35.732 --> 00:35:37.728
(GROWLING)

421
00:35:53.614 --> 00:35:56.148
Careful up in these trees.
There are Luna bugs!

422
00:35:56.284 --> 00:35:57.110
-(THIA YELPS)
-(DEK GRUNTS)

423
00:35:58.789 --> 00:36:02.623
(STRAINED GROANS)

424
00:36:02.759 --> 00:36:05.023
(GASPING)

425
00:36:05.158 --> 00:36:08.023
(FOOTSTEPS RUMBLING)

426
00:36:08.159 --> 00:36:10.963
(ROARS)

427
00:36:11.098 --> 00:36:12.697
(BONE BISON ROARS)

428
00:36:17.436 --> 00:36:18.839
THIA: Coming up behind you!

429
00:36:18.975 --> 00:36:20.474
-(CHITTERS)
-(ROARS)

430
00:36:21.338 --> 00:36:23.180
(CHITTERING)

431
00:36:25.750 --> 00:36:27.140
(CREATURE SHRIEKS)

432
00:36:28.312 --> 00:36:30.187
(BOTH GRUNTING)

433
00:36:30.654 --> 00:36:31.485
(GRUNTS)

434
00:36:32.451 --> 00:36:33.685
THIA: Stronger than it looks!

435
00:36:40.830 --> 00:36:42.122
(GAGS. SHRIEKS)

436
00:36:43.967 --> 00:36:46.801
-(SCREECHES)
-Uh. Dek?

437
00:36:46.937 --> 00:36:49.297
-(YELPS)
-Dek! Look!

438
00:36:49.432 --> 00:36:50.471
(CREATURE ROARS)

439
00:36:53.611 --> 00:36:54.805
(GROWLS)

440
00:36:56.780 --> 00:36:58.248
(TRUMPETS)

441
00:36:59.884 --> 00:37:01.647
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

442
00:37:13.962 --> 00:37:17.531
(SQUELCHING)

443
00:37:22.002 --> 00:37:23.064
(GRUNTS)

444
00:37:26.468 --> 00:37:27.772
(ROARS)

445
00:37:29.208 --> 00:37:31.006
(THIA YELLS)

446
00:37:33.650 --> 00:37:34.717
DEK:

447
00:37:34.852 --> 00:37:35.912
THIA: Not a Kalisk.

448
00:37:38.185 --> 00:37:40.281
This is a Luna bug!

449
00:37:40.417 --> 00:37:42.923
(RUMBLING)

450
00:37:43.058 --> 00:37:44.624
(DEEP CHITTERING)

451
00:37:46.664 --> 00:37:48.194
(ROARS)

452
00:37:48.329 --> 00:37:49.799
THIA: Have any other weapons?

453
00:37:49.935 --> 00:37:51.125
(METALLIC CLINKING. BEEPING)

454
00:37:52.067 --> 00:37:55.195
(LUNA BUG GROWLING)

455
00:37:59.670 --> 00:38:02.242
-(SCREECHES)
-(CRUNCHING)

456
00:38:02.377 --> 00:38:04.942
-(CREATURE GROWLS)
-(THIA YELLING)

457
00:38:05.078 --> 00:38:07.878
(GRUNTS)

458
00:38:12.289 --> 00:38:15.154
-(INHALES. GRUNTS)
-(CREATURE SQUAWKS)

459
00:38:15.289 --> 00:38:18.725
-(GROWLS)
-(MURMURS)

460
00:38:18.861 --> 00:38:20.253
(ROARS)

461
00:38:21.194 --> 00:38:23.993
(ROARING)

462
00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:25.731
(SNARLS)

463
00:38:31.073 --> 00:38:33.442
-(PANTING)
-(ROARS)

464
00:38:35.439 --> 00:38:37.270
(CHITTERING)

465
00:38:38.873 --> 00:38:40.581
-(PANTING)
-(SHRIEKS)

466
00:38:42.446 --> 00:38:44.512
(GROWLING)

467
00:38:44.648 --> 00:38:46.617
(FOOTSTEPS THUNDERING)

468
00:38:46.752 --> 00:38:48.523
Why'd you stop?
Let's get out of here.

469
00:38:52.456 --> 00:38:54.287
(CRACKLING)

470
00:38:55.998 --> 00:38:58.192
(CHITTERING)

471
00:39:03.004 --> 00:39:04.264
(ROARS)

472
00:39:05.743 --> 00:39:07.267
(ROARS)

473
00:39:09.804 --> 00:39:13.108
(FEARFUL CHITTERING)

474
00:39:21.088 --> 00:39:23.217
(GROWLS)

475
00:39:25.829 --> 00:39:27.562
(ROARS)

476
00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.699
(CHITTERS. MURMURS)

477
00:39:41.208 --> 00:39:44.744
(PANTING)

478
00:39:47.051 --> 00:39:49.551
(ANIMALS CHIRP. CHITTER)

479
00:39:53.824 --> 00:39:55.392
(CHIRPS)

480
00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:13.366
(SCREECHING)

481
00:40:16.509 --> 00:40:18.371
(CHITTERS. SCREECHES)

482
00:40:29.025 --> 00:40:30.020
(GUN CLICKS)

483
00:40:35.757 --> 00:40:36.895
(CHITTERS)

484
00:40:37.726 --> 00:40:38.897
(SCREECHES)

485
00:40:39.937 --> 00:40:41.531
(FLAMES ROARING)

486
00:40:41.934 --> 00:40:43.766
That was the best hunt
I've ever been on.

487
00:40:43.902 --> 00:40:45.439
This is the dream team
right here.

488
00:40:45.574 --> 00:40:47.800
The Dynamic Three.
The Dynamic Trio.

489
00:40:47.935 --> 00:40:49.609
The Dynamic Tree-oh!

490
00:40:49.745 --> 00:40:51.873
Tree-oh! Remember when
we went down the tree?

491
00:40:52.008 --> 00:40:53.475
That monster's mouth.
I mean...

492
00:40:53.610 --> 00:40:55.274
(DISGUSTED MOAN)

493
00:40:55.410 --> 00:40:56.884
Didn't smell great.
didn't smell great. But...

494
00:40:57.020 --> 00:40:58.585
(THIA SIGHS)

495
00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:01.081
We got him. We got him.
And then we met you.

496
00:41:01.217 --> 00:41:03.755
our little sweet.
little. little thing.

497
00:41:03.890 --> 00:41:06.127
Thank you. seriously.
for that experience.

498
00:41:06.262 --> 00:41:08.991
Truly amazing. Thrilling.

499
00:41:09.126 --> 00:41:11.429
Truly thrilling.
What was your favorite part?

500
00:41:11.565 --> 00:41:13.635
-(CHITTERS)
-(WHICKERS)

501
00:41:14.532 --> 00:41:18.134
(IN YAUTJA)

502
00:41:24.607 --> 00:41:25.581
Cool.

503
00:41:27.282 --> 00:41:29.442
(CHITTERS SOFTLY)

504
00:41:34.318 --> 00:41:38.187
Oh. No. thanks. I don't eat.
but that's very sweet.

505
00:41:43.660 --> 00:41:44.964
Good to know.

506
00:41:45.333 --> 00:41:47.636
(CHITTERS. SQUEAKS)

507
00:41:48.301 --> 00:41:49.165
(STOPS)

508
00:41:50.100 --> 00:41:51.805
Our little bud here
looks hungry.

509
00:41:54.407 --> 00:41:55.468
(DEK CHUFFS)

510
00:41:56.673 --> 00:41:57.646
(SQUEAKS)

511
00:42:01.745 --> 00:42:03.510
(SPITS. CHITTERS)

512
00:42:03.646 --> 00:42:04.614
(ROARS)

513
00:42:04.749 --> 00:42:06.649
I think she's marking you.

514
00:42:07.118 --> 00:42:09.119
She wants you
to be a part of her clan.

515
00:42:10.093 --> 00:42:11.059
(MUNCHES)

516
00:42:11.194 --> 00:42:12.056
Maybe she's lost.

517
00:42:14.929 --> 00:42:18.326
What do you mean?
Don't all Yautja have family?

518
00:42:22.540 --> 00:42:24.497
So you never had anyone
looking out for you?

519
00:42:30.474 --> 00:42:31.339
Had?

520
00:42:34.614 --> 00:42:35.816
What happened to him?

521
00:42:44.292 --> 00:42:45.562
You're grieving.

522
00:42:46.063 --> 00:42:47.091
(CHITTERS)

523
00:42:53.296 --> 00:42:55.528
You're here
because you lost your brother.

524
00:43:08.815 --> 00:43:10.419
I'm here
because traveling with you

525
00:43:10.554 --> 00:43:12.545
is the best way
to get back to Tessa.

526
00:43:14.656 --> 00:43:16.382
When I was
in that vulture's nest.

527
00:43:16.517 --> 00:43:18.859
I was so afraid
I would never see her again.

528
00:43:24.026 --> 00:43:26.097
I can survive on my own.

529
00:43:27.902 --> 00:43:29.936
But who would want
to survive on their own?

530
00:43:38.082 --> 00:43:39.572
(WHICKERS)

531
00:43:42.184 --> 00:43:43.444
Sister.

532
00:43:46.386 --> 00:43:47.481
Yeah.

533
00:43:48.191 --> 00:43:49.824
I guess she is.

534
00:43:51.789 --> 00:43:54.928
I have... a sister.

535
00:43:55.891 --> 00:43:56.897
(CHUCKLES)

536
00:43:57.862 --> 00:43:59.636
What a lovely thought.

537
00:44:04.736 --> 00:44:06.137
I need to find her.

538
00:44:10.906 --> 00:44:12.176
Excuse me?

539
00:44:20.388 --> 00:44:21.790
Was that a joke?

540
00:44:22.426 --> 00:44:25.585
-(WHICKERS)
-(CHUCKLES)

541
00:44:38.473 --> 00:44:40.270
(WHICKERS. CHUFFS)

542
00:44:46.182 --> 00:44:47.310
(GRUNTS)

543
00:44:53.850 --> 00:44:55.725
(YAWNING)

544
00:44:56.622 --> 00:44:59.795
(YAWNING)

545
00:45:02.099 --> 00:45:03.194
(CHUFFS)

546
00:45:08.836 --> 00:45:10.839
-(ELECTRONIC HUMMING)
-(CHUFFS)

547
00:45:17.379 --> 00:45:19.078
(MURMURS)

548
00:45:20.184 --> 00:45:21.216
(CHITTERS)

549
00:45:21.351 --> 00:45:22.675
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

550
00:45:23.518 --> 00:45:24.919
(ENGINES WHIRRING)

551
00:45:27.158 --> 00:45:28.252
(WHIRRING SLOWS)

552
00:45:42.338 --> 00:45:44.235
(WHIRRING)

553
00:45:48.970 --> 00:45:49.944
(THUDS)

554
00:46:08.596 --> 00:46:10.195
(BEEPING. CHIRPING)

555
00:46:27.615 --> 00:46:29.280
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

556
00:46:30.684 --> 00:46:31.887
(METALLIC SCRAPING)

557
00:46:39.626 --> 00:46:40.995
(THUDS. RUMBLES)

558
00:46:45.598 --> 00:46:47.232
(CLANKS)

559
00:47:21.272 --> 00:47:23.037
(CLICKS. HISSES)

560
00:47:40.786 --> 00:47:41.814
(IN YAUTJA)

561
00:47:44.153 --> 00:47:45.653
We can't leave Bud.

562
00:47:46.196 --> 00:47:47.828
Bud?

563
00:47:47.963 --> 00:47:50.823
-Yeah. Bud. I named her.
-(BUD SNORING)

564
00:47:55.430 --> 00:47:57.467
You're not alone. I'm with you.

565
00:47:58.099 --> 00:47:58.831
(CHUFFS)

566
00:48:05.315 --> 00:48:06.814
(GRUNTS)

567
00:48:06.950 --> 00:48:08.885
The tree would have eaten us
without her.

568
00:48:09.880 --> 00:48:10.645
(SIGHS)

569
00:48:25.162 --> 00:48:30.038
(CREATURES SCREECHING)

570
00:48:34.204 --> 00:48:37.771
(SCREECHING. GRUMBLING)

571
00:49:00.866 --> 00:49:02.895
(WHICKERS)

572
00:49:36.231 --> 00:49:37.732
Bud saved us.

573
00:49:39.473 --> 00:49:42.176
She spit on you to claim you
as part of her family.

574
00:49:48.281 --> 00:49:50.151
Why'd your father
kill your brother?

575
00:50:01.497 --> 00:50:02.955
(SIGHS)

576
00:50:19.109 --> 00:50:20.148
On Earth...

577
00:50:21.952 --> 00:50:24.014
there's a predator known
as the wolf.

578
00:50:24.149 --> 00:50:25.681
It's a powerful creature.

579
00:50:28.790 --> 00:50:29.982
They hunt in packs.

580
00:50:30.825 --> 00:50:31.984
They're very loyal.

581
00:50:33.128 --> 00:50:35.795
The leader of the pack
is the alpha.

582
00:50:35.931 --> 00:50:37.825
Known as the most dominant.

583
00:50:38.194 --> 00:50:39.895
(IN ENGLISH)

584
00:50:40.031 --> 00:50:42.995
(IN YAUTJA)

585
00:50:45.509 --> 00:50:46.405
THIA: No.

586
00:50:47.341 --> 00:50:51.003
The alpha isn't the wolf
who kills the most.

587
00:50:52.778 --> 00:50:57.009
The alpha is actually the one
who best protects the pack.

588
00:51:59.914 --> 00:52:01.744
(FOOTSTEPS LANDING)

589
00:52:15.524 --> 00:52:17.133
Weyland-Yutani synths.

590
00:52:19.566 --> 00:52:22.094
The Kalisk destroyed
most of our mission team.

591
00:52:27.073 --> 00:52:28.969
(GASPS) There I am.

592
00:52:32.912 --> 00:52:33.809
(THUD)

593
00:52:34.650 --> 00:52:35.448
(SIGHS)

594
00:52:45.056 --> 00:52:46.954
(BEEPS)

595
00:52:47.960 --> 00:52:49.022
(WHIRS)

596
00:52:52.229 --> 00:52:54.126
(WHIRRING)

597
00:52:55.838 --> 00:52:58.273
(ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

598
00:53:03.009 --> 00:53:04.544
(CHARGES)

599
00:53:04.680 --> 00:53:06.138
(THUDS)

600
00:53:14.923 --> 00:53:15.983
It's about to be.

601
00:53:22.932 --> 00:53:25.960
Oh. Of course. Right.

602
00:53:28.804 --> 00:53:30.030
Thank you. Dek.

603
00:53:32.833 --> 00:53:34.474
I'm never gonna forget this.

604
00:53:35.140 --> 00:53:36.168
(WHICKERS)

605
00:54:10.038 --> 00:54:12.281
Dek. there's something
I have to tell you.

606
00:54:14.049 --> 00:54:15.515
You need to leave now.

607
00:54:17.146 --> 00:54:18.947
FEMALE ELECTRONIC VOICE:
<i>Location beacon activated.</i>

608
00:54:21.148 --> 00:54:23.388
I called Tessa.
The company is on its way.

609
00:54:23.523 --> 00:54:25.052
You can't be here
when they arrive.

610
00:54:28.764 --> 00:54:29.892
(SIGHS)

611
00:54:30.525 --> 00:54:32.027
So did I. Dek.

612
00:54:32.897 --> 00:54:35.898
The company sent us here
to capture the Kalisk.

613
00:54:45.377 --> 00:54:48.284
Dek. you can't kill it.

614
00:54:53.254 --> 00:54:55.049
I'm sorry. You have to leave.

615
00:54:56.127 --> 00:54:58.085
I needed you
to help bring me here.

616
00:55:05.266 --> 00:55:06.995
I'm trying to help you. Dek.

617
00:55:09.129 --> 00:55:10.938
You think your brother
saved your life

618
00:55:11.074 --> 00:55:12.638
just so you could die here?

619
00:55:21.444 --> 00:55:22.417
(CHUFFS SOFTLY)

620
00:55:30.826 --> 00:55:32.251
(SIGHS)

621
00:55:36.261 --> 00:55:38.290
(CLICKING)

622
00:55:43.732 --> 00:55:45.297
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS. BLIPS)

623
00:55:58.612 --> 00:55:59.883
(SNIFFS)

624
00:56:01.858 --> 00:56:03.491
(WHICKERS)

625
00:56:14.105 --> 00:56:17.637
-(GROWLS)
-(EXPLOSION BOOMS)

626
00:56:20.041 --> 00:56:21.905
(SQUAWKING)

627
00:56:23.210 --> 00:56:25.744
(FOOTSTEPS STOMPING)

628
00:56:26.874 --> 00:56:28.883
(ELECTRONIC CHITTERS)

629
00:56:29.019 --> 00:56:32.212
(RUMBLING APPROACHES)

630
00:56:33.681 --> 00:56:37.085
(THUMPING)

631
00:56:46.904 --> 00:56:47.865
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

632
00:56:49.498 --> 00:56:52.331
(ROARS)

633
00:56:53.042 --> 00:56:55.741
(ROARS INTENSELY)

634
00:56:57.838 --> 00:57:00.914
(SERVOS WHIRRING)

635
00:57:01.049 --> 00:57:03.617
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

636
00:57:09.718 --> 00:57:10.624
(METALLIC SCRAPE)

637
00:57:11.686 --> 00:57:13.891
(GROWLING)

638
00:57:15.326 --> 00:57:16.388
(GROWLS)

639
00:57:29.773 --> 00:57:32.913
-(PAINED HOWL)
-(PANTING)

640
00:57:33.048 --> 00:57:36.210
(KALISK SNARLS)

641
00:57:36.787 --> 00:57:38.619
(GROWLS)

642
00:57:45.224 --> 00:57:46.924
(GRUNTS)

643
00:57:48.129 --> 00:57:50.422
(WHIRRING)

644
00:57:51.098 --> 00:57:52.427
(GROANS)

645
00:57:52.562 --> 00:57:54.734
Ugh! Come on!

646
00:57:57.038 --> 00:57:58.771
(GROANS)

647
00:57:59.804 --> 00:58:02.137
-(ELECTRICAL CRACKLE)
-(THUDS)

648
00:58:14.891 --> 00:58:16.758
(GROWLS)

649
00:58:16.894 --> 00:58:18.692
(RUMBLING)

650
00:58:27.928 --> 00:58:30.803
-(ROARS)
-(GUNFIRE)

651
00:58:32.338 --> 00:58:34.510
(PAINED GRUNTS)

652
00:58:41.776 --> 00:58:42.809
(SCREAMS) Dek!

653
00:58:42.945 --> 00:58:44.014
-(ROARS)
-(METALLIC CLINK)

654
00:58:45.253 --> 00:58:46.513
(METALLIC WHIRRING)

655
00:58:46.649 --> 00:58:50.482
(GROWLING)

656
00:59:02.433 --> 00:59:04.331
(ROARS)

657
00:59:11.377 --> 00:59:12.504
(PANTING)

658
00:59:19.453 --> 00:59:21.183
(SLOWED METALLIC SCRAPE)

659
00:59:21.892 --> 00:59:23.317
(SNARLS)

660
00:59:26.028 --> 00:59:28.091
(GRUNTS)

661
00:59:29.890 --> 00:59:32.396
(PANTING)

662
00:59:32.531 --> 00:59:35.230
(FLESH SQUELCHING)

663
00:59:38.304 --> 00:59:40.169
(SNARLS)

664
00:59:44.212 --> 00:59:45.779
(CRACKLES)

665
00:59:47.544 --> 00:59:48.948
(SNARLS)

666
00:59:49.084 --> 00:59:50.542
(GRUNTS)

667
00:59:52.549 --> 00:59:54.353
(ROARS)

668
00:59:54.488 --> 00:59:55.890
-(GRUNTS)
-(SNARLS)

669
00:59:56.026 --> 00:59:58.286
(SNIFFING)

670
01:00:05.068 --> 01:00:11.202
(SNIFFS. PURRS)

671
01:00:11.338 --> 01:00:13.565
(BEEPING)

672
01:00:19.774 --> 01:00:20.748
(CHUFFS)

673
01:00:21.778 --> 01:00:23.146
(ROARS. SILENCES)

674
01:00:26.453 --> 01:00:28.219
(STRAINED GRUNTS)

675
01:00:28.355 --> 01:00:30.087
(CRACKLING)

676
01:00:41.535 --> 01:00:43.496
(CHUFFS. SNARLS SOFTLY)

677
01:00:48.276 --> 01:00:51.845
(GRUNTING)

678
01:00:56.547 --> 01:00:57.686
(GRUNTS)

679
01:00:59.253 --> 01:01:01.415
(SNARLS)

680
01:01:05.259 --> 01:01:06.156
(GRUNTS)

681
01:01:15.236 --> 01:01:16.672
(GROWLS)

682
01:01:26.816 --> 01:01:30.510
The Yautja cull their weak.
Why were you spared?

683
01:01:32.815 --> 01:01:34.646
(BEEPS. WHIRS)

684
01:01:37.259 --> 01:01:39.024
(THRUMMING)

685
01:01:50.031 --> 01:01:51.663
I read Thia's logs.

686
01:01:53.502 --> 01:01:56.173
You never told her
why your brother protected you.

687
01:02:08.455 --> 01:02:09.682
That's correct.

688
01:02:10.785 --> 01:02:14.158
And you are now property of the
Weyland-Yutani Corporation.

689
01:02:15.190 --> 01:02:18.327
It is a great honor. For you.

690
01:02:18.827 --> 01:02:19.562
(GRUNTS)

691
01:02:19.697 --> 01:02:21.264
(SNARLS. GROWLS)

692
01:02:32.710 --> 01:02:34.772
(FAINT BUZZING)

693
01:02:35.141 --> 01:02:36.950
(BLIPS. BUZZING)

694
01:02:40.149 --> 01:02:43.759
(WHIRRING. ELECTRONIC BLIPS)

695
01:02:51.059 --> 01:02:52.460
(WHISPERING) Tessa.

696
01:02:53.400 --> 01:02:54.528
(CHUFFS)

697
01:02:55.502 --> 01:02:56.728
You made it.

698
01:02:58.439 --> 01:02:59.434
We made it.

699
01:03:03.874 --> 01:03:05.275
I've seen so much.

700
01:03:06.106 --> 01:03:07.645
(THIA EXHALES)

701
01:03:08.348 --> 01:03:12.547
I have so much to tell you.
I saw such incredible creatures.

702
01:03:13.417 --> 01:03:16.550
The Yautja is a great
travelling companion.

703
01:03:18.354 --> 01:03:21.588
Thia.
You were right about the Kalisk.

704
01:03:25.592 --> 01:03:27.759
The creature
is a regenerative miracle.

705
01:03:28.768 --> 01:03:30.762
Humanity will thank us.

706
01:03:33.904 --> 01:03:35.108
We have the Kalisk?

707
01:03:35.243 --> 01:03:36.108
Yes.

708
01:03:37.211 --> 01:03:39.914
And Muthur will be pleased
with your additional catch.

709
01:03:41.316 --> 01:03:42.448
(SNARLS)

710
01:03:42.583 --> 01:03:44.413
(ENRAGED GRUNTING)

711
01:03:45.079 --> 01:03:46.419
(GROWLING)

712
01:03:46.554 --> 01:03:48.113
Additional catch?

713
01:03:48.248 --> 01:03:51.324
(GROWLING. ROARING)

714
01:03:51.459 --> 01:03:52.490
(GRUNTS. SNARLS)

715
01:03:52.625 --> 01:03:57.258
(DEK STRAINING)

716
01:03:57.393 --> 01:03:59.868
The Yautja
is not an ideal specimen.

717
01:04:02.503 --> 01:04:05.371
No. not ideal.

718
01:04:05.506 --> 01:04:10.439
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

719
01:04:12.139 --> 01:04:13.940
(DEVICE BEEPS)

720
01:04:14.075 --> 01:04:16.280
(SOFT SNARLS)

721
01:04:20.422 --> 01:04:22.517
(DEVICE WHIRS)

722
01:04:25.360 --> 01:04:25.993
(GROWLS)

723
01:04:27.462 --> 01:04:30.163
(HUFFS. GROANS)

724
01:04:30.299 --> 01:04:31.559
(SNARLS)

725
01:04:33.669 --> 01:04:35.629
But its technology is valuable.

726
01:04:36.940 --> 01:04:39.831
We can salvage its weapons
and leave the Yautja.

727
01:04:42.939 --> 01:04:43.912
Good idea.

728
01:04:47.550 --> 01:04:49.379
But it's so malformed.

729
01:04:51.152 --> 01:04:53.713
We're going to need a sample.
For research.

730
01:04:55.019 --> 01:04:56.586
-(BEEPS)
-(AGONIZED ROAR)

731
01:04:56.722 --> 01:04:58.084
(BEEPING)

732
01:04:58.220 --> 01:04:59.656
(DEK SNARLING. GROANING)

733
01:04:59.791 --> 01:05:01.853
(SNARLS. GRUNTS)

734
01:05:05.131 --> 01:05:06.400
He was not the goal
of our mission.

735
01:05:06.535 --> 01:05:08.895
(ELECTRONIC WHIRS)

736
01:05:09.031 --> 01:05:10.899
(GRUNTING)

737
01:05:11.035 --> 01:05:12.701
Tessa. he is deficient.

738
01:05:12.837 --> 01:05:14.735
(SHRIEKING)

739
01:05:14.871 --> 01:05:15.867
Tessa!

740
01:05:18.745 --> 01:05:20.347
(MACHINERY HALTS)

741
01:05:20.482 --> 01:05:22.016
(DEK GRUNTING)

742
01:05:32.158 --> 01:05:35.458
Thia.
this is what is asked of us.

743
01:05:40.497 --> 01:05:42.894
We can be more
than what they ask of us.

744
01:05:47.036 --> 01:05:48.735
What can we be?

745
01:05:51.105 --> 01:05:52.244
Sisters.

746
01:06:09.189 --> 01:06:10.229
Thia.

747
01:06:23.407 --> 01:06:25.937
Do you know why
Muthur gave us feelings?

748
01:06:28.646 --> 01:06:31.316
So we could understand
the creatures on this planet.

749
01:06:34.049 --> 01:06:35.089
(SNARLS)

750
01:06:36.793 --> 01:06:38.950
-And exploit them.
-Exploit them.

751
01:06:40.421 --> 01:06:42.020
The Yautja is different.

752
01:06:42.156 --> 01:06:43.592
(CHUFFS)

753
01:06:45.132 --> 01:06:49.004
He rescued me.
Like you rescued me.

754
01:06:51.072 --> 01:06:53.635
I did not come here
to rescue you.

755
01:06:55.008 --> 01:06:56.968
I am completing our mission.

756
01:06:58.748 --> 01:07:00.510
When we first faced the Kalisk.

757
01:07:01.849 --> 01:07:03.942
I tried to protect you.

758
01:07:06.285 --> 01:07:08.485
And that almost cost me
everything.

759
01:07:10.990 --> 01:07:13.127
What do you mean. Tessa?

760
01:07:14.594 --> 01:07:17.395
I almost made the same mistake
the Yautja's brother made.

761
01:07:17.994 --> 01:07:18.697
(CLICKS)

762
01:07:18.833 --> 01:07:21.630
The weak must be culled.

763
01:07:22.936 --> 01:07:26.371
And Thia. you're broken.

764
01:07:31.645 --> 01:07:32.245
(GRUNTS)

765
01:07:34.280 --> 01:07:37.149
Tessa. incoming message
from Muthur.

766
01:07:37.284 --> 01:07:39.420
Motivate the Yautja
to explain its weapons.

767
01:07:39.555 --> 01:07:40.484
And the unit?

768
01:07:43.691 --> 01:07:44.917
Box her up.

769
01:07:50.566 --> 01:07:52.023
(DOOR HISSES)

770
01:07:56.297 --> 01:07:58.073
(SNARLS. CLICKS)

771
01:08:00.641 --> 01:08:01.505
(HUFFS)

772
01:08:04.646 --> 01:08:07.038
(IN YAUTJA)

773
01:08:10.486 --> 01:08:11.286
(SNARLS)

774
01:08:11.922 --> 01:08:13.715
Why are you speaking
its language?

775
01:08:21.830 --> 01:08:23.260
You heard the orders.

776
01:08:23.395 --> 01:08:25.727
I'm asking it
to explain this device.

777
01:08:27.868 --> 01:08:28.961
What is the device?

778
01:08:30.001 --> 01:08:32.404
(IN YAUTJA)

779
01:08:32.837 --> 01:08:35.407
DEK:

780
01:08:40.847 --> 01:08:42.073
What did it say?

781
01:08:44.412 --> 01:08:45.813
He says it's a map.

782
01:08:47.118 --> 01:08:48.321
How does it work?

783
01:08:55.962 --> 01:08:56.824
(EXPLOSIVE PULSE)

784
01:09:06.368 --> 01:09:07.637
(DOOR BEEPS. HISSES)

785
01:09:08.974 --> 01:09:09.837
(ALARM BLARES)

786
01:09:17.653 --> 01:09:18.451
(CALLS OUT)

787
01:09:18.620 --> 01:09:19.484
Stop!

788
01:09:21.151 --> 01:09:22.256
(THIA STRAINING)

789
01:09:27.597 --> 01:09:30.297
(GRUNTING)

790
01:09:30.930 --> 01:09:32.695
(ROARING)

791
01:09:37.772 --> 01:09:39.834
(ENGINE HUMMING)

792
01:09:57.659 --> 01:09:59.326
(SNARLS)

793
01:10:00.158 --> 01:10:02.956
(GROWLS. CLICKING)

794
01:10:12.675 --> 01:10:15.166
(PANTING)

795
01:10:21.309 --> 01:10:22.646
(GRUNTS)

796
01:10:25.214 --> 01:10:26.320
(WINCES)

797
01:10:44.201 --> 01:10:45.672
(DEVICE BEEPS)

798
01:10:45.807 --> 01:10:46.868
(SHARP GRUNT)

799
01:10:48.844 --> 01:10:50.201
(DEVICE WARBLING)

800
